    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop the<strong> tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> roughly </p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
