    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> vegetable stock</strong> and<strong> browned meat-free mince meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>meat-free mince meatball masala</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
