      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the sauce is thickening, wash the<strong> spinach</strong>, then add it to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach </strong>under the cold tap until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze the water out of the spinach as much as you can</p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, stir the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> through the masala</p>",
